title: For Sale:  S&W .32 Long "regulation police"
postcontent: This is a fully functional Pre-War Smith & Wesson .32 long "Regulation Police" revolver. i haven't been able to look up is exact age but judging from dates on similarly numbered pistols I've found im guessing it's 30's to 40's. It's in great shape for it's age. It locks up tight and looks as if it has been fired very, very little. The bore is pristine and there is almost no cylinder ring on this thing. The previous owner did let the pistol get dry at some point over the years so there was a small bit of light surface rust on one side of the end of the barrel when I got it. It has since been well lubed and is hardly noticable. You can see from the pics that the plastic pearl grips have shrunk a little over the years but still function fine. That's all I can think of.. If you'd like to see it in person email me through this ad and we'll get together. Can meet in Jacksonville most days. I'm listing this at a steal for 250 obo. It's a great, fully functional peice of prohibition era history, It's just not my cup of tea.. Feel free to offer up any firearm trades. I'm mostly into pistols but a nice .38 or 357 snubby might catch my eye as well. Maybe a decent shotgun? Cash.. who knows... never hurts to ask. Thanks
